# Peer AI Development Workflow

This repository contains the Peer AI development playbook — a portable, agent-agnostic workflow for AI-assisted software development. When a user asks about process, standards, or how to do something, reference the relevant workflow document.

## Quick reference

| Need | Document |
|------|----------|
| Break down requirements | `shared/01-understand.md` |
| Design architecture | `shared/02-architect.md` |
| Write a PM spec | `shared/03-spec-system.md` |
| Define API contracts | `shared/04-spec-api-contract.md` |
| Coding standards | `shared/05-rules-shared.md` |
| Create issues | `shared/06-issues.md` |
| Write documentation | `shared/07-document.md` |
| Set up PR automation | `shared/09-pr-automation.md` |
| Dev journal & retrospective | `shared/08-dev-journal.md` |
| Workflow state + CONTEXT pattern | `shared/workflow-state.md` |
| Design vs data contract conflicts | `shared/design-data-contract.md` |
| Ambient workflow driver | `shared/cursor-rules/workflow-driver.mdc` |
| Define frontend pages | `frontend/01-spec-pages.md` |
| Frontend coding rules | `frontend/02-rules.md` |
| Build frontend features | `frontend/03-build.md` |
| Review frontend code | `frontend/04-review.md` |
| Test frontend code | `frontend/05-test.md` |
